{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"16154","heading":"Clean hydrogen research and development program","label":"16154 Clean hydrogen research and development program","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/ch149/schVIII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Amendments2021—, substituted “Clean hydrogen research and development program” for “Programs” in section catchline.Pub. L. 117–58, § 40313(a)(1)Subsec. (a). , substituted “crosscutting research and development program (referred to in this section as the ‘program’)” for “research and development program” and inserted “processing,” after “production,”.Pub. L. 117–58, § 40313(a)(2)Subsec. (b). , added subsec. (b) and struck out former subsec. (b). Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The goal of the program shall be to demonstrate and commercialize the use of hydrogen for transportation (in light-duty vehicles and heavy-duty vehicles), utility, industrial, commercial, and residential applications.”Pub. L. 117–58, § 40313(a)(3)Subsec. (c)(3). , substituted “fossil fuels with carbon capture, utilization, and sequestration, renewable fuels, biofuels, and nuclear energy” for “renewable fuels and biofuels”.Pub. L. 117–58, § 40313(a)(4)Subsec. (e). , added subsec. (e) and struck out former subsec. (e) which required Secretary, in partnership with private sector, to conduct programs to address certain activities.Pub. L. 117–58, § 40313(a)(5)Subsec. (j). , added subsec. (j).Pub. L. 117–58, § 40313(a)(6)","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Wage Rate RequirementsFor provisions relating to rates of wages to be paid to laborers and mechanics on projects for construction, alteration, or repair work funded under div. D or an amendment by div. D of , including authority of Secretary of Labor, see .Pub. L. 117–58section 18851 of this title"],"amendments":["Amendments2021—, substituted “Clean hydrogen research and development program” for “Programs” in section catchline.Pub. L. 117–58, § 40313(a)(1)Subsec. (a). , substituted “crosscutting research and development program (referred to in this section as the ‘program’)” for “research and development program” and inserted “processing,” after “production,”.Pub. L. 117–58, § 40313(a)(2)Subsec. (b). , added subsec. (b) and struck out former subsec. (b). Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The goal of the program shall be to demonstrate and commercialize the use of hydrogen for transportation (in light-duty vehicles and heavy-duty vehicles), utility, industrial, commercial, and residential applications.”Pub. L. 117–58, § 40313(a)(3)Subsec. (c)(3). , substituted “fossil fuels with carbon capture, utilization, and sequestration, renewable fuels, biofuels, and nuclear energy” for “renewable fuels and biofuels”.Pub. L. 117–58, § 40313(a)(4)Subsec. (e). , added subsec. (e) and struck out former subsec. (e) which required Secretary, in partnership with private sector, to conduct programs to address certain activities.Pub. L. 117–58, § 40313(a)(5)Subsec. (j). , added subsec. (j).Pub. L. 117–58, § 40313(a)(6)","Wage Rate RequirementsFor provisions relating to rates of wages to be paid to laborers and mechanics on projects for construction, alteration, or repair work funded under div. D or an amendment by div. D of , including authority of Secretary of Labor, see .Pub. L. 117–58section 18851 of this title"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"In general","label":"a In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary, in consultation with other Federal agencies and the private sector, shall conduct a crosscutting research and development program (referred to in this section as the “program”) on technologies relating to the production, processing, purification, distribution, storage, and use of hydrogen energy, fuel cells, and related infrastructure.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Goals","label":"b Goals","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to advance research and development to demonstrate and commercialize the use of clean hydrogen in the transportation, utility, industrial, commercial, and residential sectors; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to demonstrate a standard of clean hydrogen production in the transportation, utility, industrial, commercial, and residential sectors by 2040.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Focus","label":"c Focus","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"steadily increase production, distribution, and end use efficiency and reduce life-cycle emissions;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"resolve critical problems relating to catalysts, membranes, storage, lightweight materials, electronic controls, manufacturability, and other problems that emerge from the program;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"enhance sources of fossil fuels with carbon capture, utilization, and sequestration, renewable fuels, biofuels, and nuclear energy for hydrogen production; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/c/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fc%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"enable widespread use of distributed electricity generation and storage.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Public education and research","label":"d Public education and research","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In carrying out this section, the Secretary shall support enhanced public education and research conducted at institutions of higher education in fundamental sciences, application design, and systems concepts (including education and research relating to materials, subsystems, manufacturability, maintenance, and safety) relating to hydrogen and fuel cells.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":"Activities","label":"e Activities","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the establishment of a series of technology cost goals oriented toward achieving the standard of clean hydrogen production developed under ;section 16166(a) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"fossil fuels with carbon capture, utilization, and sequestration;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"hydrogen-carrier fuels (including ethanol and methanol);","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"renewable energy resources, including biomass;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/2/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F2%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"nuclear energy; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/2/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F2%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any other methods the Secretary determines to be appropriate;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the use of clean hydrogen for commercial, industrial, and residential electric power generation;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the use of clean hydrogen in industrial applications, including steelmaking, cement, chemical feedstocks, and process heat;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the use of clean hydrogen for use as a fuel source for both residential and commercial comfort heating and hot water requirements;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/6/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F6%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"transmission by pipelines, including retrofitting the existing natural gas transportation infrastructure system to enable a transition to transport and deliver increasing levels of clean hydrogen, clean hydrogen blends, or clean hydrogen carriers;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/6/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F6%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"tanks and other distribution methods; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/6/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F6%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/6/C/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/6/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F6%2FC%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"at central refueling stations; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/6/C/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/6/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F6%2FC%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"through distributed onsite generation;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":null,"label":"7","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/7/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F7%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"engine and emission control systems;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/7/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F7%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"energy storage, electric propulsion, and hybrid systems;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/7/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F7%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"automotive, locomotive, maritime vessel, or plane materials; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/7/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F7%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"other advanced vehicle, locomotive, maritime vessel, or plane technologies;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"8","heading":null,"label":"8","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/8","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F8","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"storage of hydrogen or hydrogen-carrier fuels, including the development of materials for safe and economic storage in gaseous, liquid, or solid form;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"9","heading":null,"label":"9","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/9","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F9","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the development of safe, durable, affordable, and efficient fuel cells, including fuel-flexible fuel cell power systems, improved manufacturing processes, high-temperature membranes, cost-effective fuel processing for natural gas, fuel cell stack and system reliability, low-temperature operation, and cold start capability;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"10","heading":null,"label":"10","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/10","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F10","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the ability of domestic clean hydrogen equipment manufacturers to manufacture commercially available competitive technologies in the United States;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"11","heading":null,"label":"11","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/11","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F11","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the use of clean hydrogen in the transportation sector, including in light-, medium-, and heavy-duty vehicles, rail transport, aviation, and maritime applications; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"12","heading":null,"label":"12","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e/12","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Fe%2F12","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"in coordination with relevant agencies, the development of appropriate, uniform codes and standards for the safe and consistent deployment and commercialization of clean hydrogen production, processing, delivery, and end-use technologies.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"f","heading":"Program goals","label":"f Program goals","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/f","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Ff","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Vehicles","label":"1 Vehicles","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/f/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Ff%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/f/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/f/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Ff%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to enable a commitment by automakers no later than year 2015 to offer safe, affordable, and technically viable hydrogen fuel cell vehicles in the mass consumer market; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/f/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/f/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Ff%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/f/1/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/f/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Ff%2F1%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"fuel economy that is substantially higher;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/f/1/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/f/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Ff%2F1%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"substantially lower emissions of air pollutants; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/f/1/B/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/f/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16154%2Ff%2F1%2FB%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"equivalent or improved vehicle fuel system crash integrity and occupant protection.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Hydrogen energy and energy infrastructure","label":"2 Hydrogen energy and energy infrastructure","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/f/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16154/f","sourceU